<h4 data-index="4800"><span class="red" data-index="4801">Instructions</span></h4>
<p class="latin1" id="c22-ex-0259" data-index="4802"><span class="label" data-index="4803"><b data-index="4804">a.</b>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span> Assuming that the tax rate is 20%, what is the amount of net income that would be reported in 2021?</p>
<p class="latin1" id="c22-ex-0260" data-index="4805"><span class="label" data-index="4806"><b data-index="4807">b.</b>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span> What entry(ies) are necessary to adjust the accounting records for the change in accounting principle?</p>
<p id="c22-ex-0261" data-index="4808"><b data-index="4809"><span class="codeColorBlue2" data-index="4810">E22.2</span></b> <b class="red" data-index="4811">(LO <a href="#lo_1" data-index="4812" data-section-index="32" data-section-idref="lo_1" data-target-data-index="148">1</a>)</b> <b data-index="4813">(Change in Principle—Inventory Methods)</b> Holder-Webb Company began operations on January 1, 2018, and uses the average-cost method of pricing inventory. Management is contemplating a change in inventory methods for 2021. The following information is available for the years 2018–2020.</p>
