<h4 data-index="6479"><span class="red" data-index="6480">Instructions</span></h4>
<p class="latin1" id="c22-ex-0341" data-index="6481"><span class="label" data-index="6482"><b data-index="6483">a.</b>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span> Indicate how each of these changes or corrections should be handled in the accounting records. (Ignore income tax considerations.)</p>
<p class="latin1" id="c22-ex-0342" data-index="6484"><span class="label" data-index="6485"><b data-index="6486">b.</b>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span> Present net income as reported in comparative income statements for the years 2018 to 2021.</p>
<p id="c22-ex-0343" data-index="6487"><b data-index="6488"><span class="codeColorBlue2" data-index="6489">P22.4</span></b> <b class="red" data-index="6490">(LO <a href="#lo_1" data-index="6491" data-section-index="32" data-section-idref="lo_1" data-target-data-index="148">1</a>, <a href="#lo_2" data-index="6492" data-section-index="32" data-section-idref="lo_2" data-target-data-index="1996">2</a>, <a href="#lo_3" data-index="6493" data-section-index="32" data-section-idref="lo_3" data-target-data-index="2234">3</a>)</b> <b data-index="6494">(Error Corrections and Accounting Changes)</b> Penn Company is in the process of adjusting and correcting its books at the end of 2020. In reviewing its records, the following information is compiled.</p>
